      "- Class II: Load is in the middle.",
      "- Class III: Effort is in the middle."
    ],
    "questionText": "1. A cable drum has a mass of 25kg. Calculate the weight force it exerts on the floor in Newtons. \n2. You are using a conduit bender to bend a piece of 20mm steel conduit. In this tool, the load (the conduit) is positioned between the pivot point and the handle where you apply effort. Which class of lever is this?",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "245.25 N",
      "Class II"
    ],
    "hint": "Multiply 25 by 9.81 for the weight. For the lever, if the load is in the middle, it follows the Class II rule."
  },
  "practice": {
    "title": "Practice",
    "objective": "Determine weight from mass and categorize a Class III lever independently.",
    "retrievalTextLines": [
      "Apply the standard gravity constant of 9.81 m/s² for all weight calculations.",
      "Recall the 'middle' rule for lever classification: Pivot (I), Load (II), or Effort (III)."
    ],
    "questionText": "1. An industrial light fitting has a mass of 12kg. What is the weight force, in Newtons, that the ceiling fixings must be able to support? \n2. When using a pair of tweezers to pick up a small fuse, you apply the effort (your grip) in the middle, between the pivot at the end and the load (the fuse) at the tips. What class of lever is this?",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "117.72 N",
      "Class III"
    ],
    "hint": "Weight = Mass x 9.81. For the lever, identify which of the three components is located between the other two."
  }
}

